    <summary>Describes the placement of where a <see cref="T:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup" /> control appears on the screen.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 Use the members of this enumeration class to set the value of the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup.Placement%2A> property of a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup> control. The <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup.Placement%2A> property value, together with the values of the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup.PlacementTarget%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup.PlacementRectangle%2A>, <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup.HorizontalOffset%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup.VerticalOffset%2A>properties, determines where and how a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup> appears on the screen. For more information, see [Popup Placement Behavior](../Topic/Popup%20Placement%20Behavior.md).  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 The following example creates four <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup> controls that are relative to an image. Each <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.Popup> has a different value for the placement property.  
  
